Heat oven to 425 degrees F. Spray large cookie sheet with cooking spray. Unroll pizza dough on cookie sheet; press into 15x12-inch rectangle. Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until light golden brown. Meanwhile, microwave frozen potatoes 3 to 4 minutes to thaw. In medium bowl, using fork, mash potatoes, leaving some small pieces. Stir in 1/2 cup cooking sauce. Spread remaining cooking sauce evenly over partially baked crust. Spoon potato mixture over sauce. Sprinkle with bacon and cheese. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until crust is golden brown. Sprinkle with tomatoes and green onions.